CHANGES IN VERSION 1.39.3
-------------------------

SIGNIFICANT USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

	- Milestone 2 (Matrix ABI & rhdf5 Dependency Stabilisation):

DEPENDENCY CHANGES

	- Bumped Matrix dependency from (>= 1.2) to (>= 1.7-0) in DESCRIPTION.
	  This pins against the post-SuiteSparse ABI break and prevents runtime
	  crashes caused by binary incompatibilities in upstream sparse-matrix
	  libraries on BBS nodes running R 4.4+.

BUG FIXES

	- read_hdf5_biom(): added a requireNamespace("rhdf5", quietly = TRUE)
	  guard at the top of the function. If rhdf5 is not installed, or if
	  its underlying HDF5 system libraries are absent (common on stripped
	  BBS nodes), the function now emits a clear R-level warning and returns
	  NULL instead of producing a fatal C-level abort.

	- read_hdf5_biom(): wrapped the h5read() call in tryCatch() so that any
	  C-level or system-library error is caught and re-emitted as an R
	  warning, keeping the session alive.

	- read_biom(): replaced the fragile JSON-first / HDF5-fallback heuristic
	  with a deterministic magic-bytes check. The function now reads the first
	  4 bytes of the file: if the HDF5 signature (\x89HDF) is detected, it
	  routes exclusively to the HDF5 parser and never attempts jsonlite
	  parsing. JSON files route exclusively to jsonlite. This eliminates the
	  confusing "lexical error" that users encountered when HDF5 files were
	  accidentally passed through the JSON parser first.

	- Replaced direct rhdf5::h5read() call (via @importFrom) in
	  read_hdf5_biom() with the rhdf5::h5read() namespace-qualified call,
	  consistent with the new requireNamespace() guard pattern.


	- Milestone 1 (BBS Rescue - C-Level API Compliance):
	  Confirmed biomformat contains no compiled C/C++/Fortran code
	  (NeedsCompilation: no; no src/ directory). The package therefore
	  requires no changes for R_Calloc/R_Realloc/R_Free or Rf_allocVector
	  API compliance -- there are zero legacy C macros to replace.

BUG FIXES

	- Fixed fatal test failure under testthat >= 3.0: replaced all
	  deprecated expect_that(x, is_true()), expect_that(x, is_identical_to(y)),
	  and expect_that(x, is_a("cls")) calls in tests/testthat/test-IO.R with
	  their modern equivalents (expect_true(), expect_identical(),
	  expect_true(is(x, "cls"))). This resolves the ERROR in R CMD check
	  that was the primary BBS deprecation trigger.

	- Added missing importFrom(stats, setNames) and
	  importFrom(utils, packageVersion) directives to NAMESPACE, resolving
	  "no visible global function definition" NOTEs from R CMD check.

	- Updated Date field in DESCRIPTION to current date (2026-03-14).

CHANGES IN VERSION 0.3.13
-------------------------

USER-VISIBLE CHANGES

	- Added make_biom function. Creates biom object from standard R data table(s).

